      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Book of accounts for large lots of all types and sizes of
         shoes sold in southeastern England, especially Kent, to
         customers who included Mrs. Clark, Mrs. Sarah Culmer, Mrs.
         Friday, Thomas Hamilton, Richard Ide, Edward Jackson, Mrs.
         Sarah Palmer, Mrs. Rebecca Patience, William Simmons, Mrs.
         Susanna Simson, John Sole, and Mrs. Catherine Walk. There are
         also a few accounts in connection with the estate of Mrs. Ann
         Kemp of Ramsgate.</p>
      </scopecontent>
